The paper discusses the development of new consensus protocols for blockchain, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also addresses the scalability issue in leader election, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a protocol that provides game-theoretic guarantees, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of blockchain also involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and the incentivization aspect relates to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
